# Project Guidelines

## Documentation Requirements

-   Update relevant documentation in /docs when modifying features
-   Keep README.md in sync with new capabilities
-   Read md files in /docs for context on project structure and guidelines

## Architecture Decision Records

Create ADRs in /docs/adr for:

-   Major dependency changes
-   Architectural pattern changes
-   New integration patterns

## Code Style & Patterns

-   Follow C# coding conventions
-   Use consistent naming conventions for files, classes, and methods
-   Use `async`/`await` for asynchronous methods

## Testing Standards

-   After implmenting small chunks of tests, run all tests to ensure nothing is broken. The commands are 
    ```bash
    # Build the project
    & "C:\Program Files\Microsoft Visual Studio\2022\Community\MSBuild\Current\Bin\MSBuild.exe" MI_GUI_WinUI.Tests\MI_GUI_WinUI.Tests.csproj

    # Run all tests
    & "C:\Program Files\Microsoft Visual Studio\2022\Community\Common7\IDE\CommonExtensions\Microsoft\TestWindow\VsTest.Console.exe" "MI_GUI_WinUI.Tests\bin\x64\Release\net8.0-windows10.0.22621.0\MI_GUI_WinUI.Tests.dll"
    ```
-   Make sure to follow the test plan structure and naming conventions